December 27, 2011 Tuesday 1:32 PM GMT
Huntington research camp limits in wake of protest
SECTION: STATE AND REGIONAL
LENGTH: 137 words
DATELINE: HUNTINGTON W.Va.


Huntington officers are thinking about requiring a allow to camp on public property following an eight-week encampment by means of neighborhood Occupy activists in the front of a bank.
City Council plans to talk about the proposed ordinance at its Tuesday night time meeting.
Police Chief Skip Holbrook tells The Herald-Dispatch ( http://bit.ly/nzOvU5 ) that an ordinance would assist information regulation enforcement and provide clear regulations to protesters in the future.
Mayor Kim Wolfe evicted the Occupy Huntington protesters from their camp in front of the Chase Building Bank until now this month.
Wolfe says town officials by no means intended to restriction the group's proper to protest but there were health and safety issues. He says the city didn't have something on the books to tackle such circumstances.
Information from: The Herald-Dispatch, http://www.herald-dispatch.com


